**Why:**  
- Breaks static tooling (`nixd`, `nil`)  
- Hides scope/causes IDE completion failures  
- Reduces code readability

```nix
# ❌ BAD
environment.systemPackages = with pkgs; [ git vim ];
meta = with lib; { license = licenses.mit; };
# ✅ GOOD
environment.systemPackages = [ pkgs.git pkgs.vim ];
meta = { license = lib.licenses.mit; };
```

## Core Principles

```markdown
- Explicit > Implicit attribute paths
- Pure, declarative functional design
- Use let-in, never rec
- Format: `nixfmt`
- Destructure args, never use `with`
```
